The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, April 14, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Wednesday, April 14, 2004				 																Poila Baisakh 				 																																	Srikanta Acharya, Bratati Bandopadhyay, Buddhadeb Guha, Peeyush Ganguly and Mita Haque will feature in a cultural function at Madhusudan Mancha, 10 am onwards.				 																																	A performance by Bhoomi to celebrate the Bengali New Year, at Calcutta Club, 5 pm onwards.				 																																	A programme of folk dances, Vasundhara, to mark Vishuba Sankranti, organised by Eastern Zonal Cultural Centre, at Bharatiyam, 6.30 pm.				 																																	Bangla band Srishti will perform at Inox, 5.30 pm to 7 pm, amidst other traditional festivities.				 																																	Poila Baisakh and Baisakhi celebrations over lunch and dinner for members at Hindusthan Club.				 																																	Rabindrasangeet by Manoj Murali Nair and Manisha Murali Nair at Brahmo Sammilani Samaj, 8.30 am onwards.				 																																	A solo recital by Pramita Mallick, hosted by Sri Aurobindo Institute of Culture, on its premises, at 10 am.				 																In camera				 																																	Sandip Ray will launch a VCD of Satyajit Rays Seemabaddha at Landmark as part of the stores Bengali New Year celebrations. 				 																																	Wild Bengal, a book of selected photographs by cardiologist Debal Sen, will be launched by chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee at Hyatt Regency, at 6.30 pm.
